parameters:
Oh? You can't pass through here. You either need to be a explorer
yourself or come with a companion of an explorer.

The current party does not have any explorers. If you want to go to
the ruins, \c[6]you must have at least one companion who is an
explorer\c[0]. Alternatively, \c[6]Enicia must obtain explorer
qualifications\c[0].

Due to management reasons, permission to explore the ruins is limited
to \c[6]once a day\c[0]. Today, please take care.

Discoveries from ruins such as weapons, ancient magic books, etc. are
basically owned by the discoverer. However, ownership of valuable
treasures and important historical materials belongs to the lord.

Please make sure to sell such items to the ruins supervisor who is
staying at the Exploration Association. If you sell them through
illegal channels, you will be treated as a looter.

Discoveries from ruins such as weapons, ancient magic books, etc. are
basically owned by the discoverer. However, ownership of valuable
treasures and important historical materials belongs to the lord.

Oh, you... You are exempt from the daily exploration limit, so feel
free to explore as much as you like.

It is believed that Dearshil has been thoroughly searched, so only
fellow explorers in this area know about the unexplored floors.

If it becomes known, a lot of people from other places will come
flocking. If you want to make a fortune with treasure, now is the
time.

That being said, I'll do this. It seems to be a magic dictionary...
but it's mostly blank. It's a strange thing that records the weapons
and armor obtained.

Hm? I'm not really interested in anything other than treasure. Well,
if I keep exploring, I'll eventually find the same thing again.

It is believed that Dearshil has been thoroughly searched, so only
fellow explorers in this area know about the unexplored floors.

If it becomes known, a lot of people from other places will come
flocking. If you want to make a fortune with treasure, now is the
time.

By the way, how about the dictionary? It's all about luck whether you
can find treasure or not, so I don't think you need to try too hard to
dig it up.
